com.infinitydb.map.visitor

Class VisitableArrayWrapper<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.infinitydb.map.visitor.Visitable<java.lang.Long,V>
      • com.infinitydb.map.visitor.VisitableArrayWrapper<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VisitableMap<java.lang.Long,V>

    public class VisitableArrayWrapper<V>
extends Visitable<java.lang.Long,V>
    Make an array visitable as a series of key/value pairs using forEach(key, value) where the key is the index and the value is the array element.

    This allows a combination of arrays with various MapVisitor subclasses that can do various bulk operations conveniently, allowing a growing number of visitable things to be combined with a growing number of kinds of visitors.

    The idiom is: 

     new VisitableArrayWrapper(array).forEach(someVisitor);
    or if a SummingVisitor has been created: 
     new SummingMapVisitor().getSum(new VisitableArrayWrapper(map));

    where the someVisitor might be a SummingMapVisitor or PrintingMapVisitor or a MaxMapVisitor and son on. One advantage of this is that the visitor classes can be reused for various purposes with regular Maps, or especially AirConcurrentMap or NitroMap (in progress) or OxyMap (in progress), or Visitables like this one which are actually Map subclasses, but which can only do forEach().

    Some day, VisitableArrayWrapper may handle multi-threading when the mapVisitor parameter to forEach(MapVisitor mapVisitor) is a subclass of ThreadedMapVisitor, and possibly remoting also.

    Author:
    Roger
    See Also:
    Visitable, VisitableListWrapper, VisitableSetWrapper, VisitableMapWrapper, MapVisitor, ThreadedMapVisitor, AirConcurrentMap
